
Overview of verb believe

The verb believe has 5 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (118) believe -- (accept as true; take to be true; "I believed his report"; "We didn't believe his stories from the War"; "She believes in spirits")
2. (72) think, believe, consider, conceive -- (judge or regard; look upon; judge; "I think he is very smart"; "I believe her to be very smart"; "I think that he is her boyfriend"; "The racist conceives such people to be inferior")
3. (37) believe, trust -- (be confident about something; "I believe that he will come back from the war")
4. (10) believe -- (follow a credo; have a faith; be a believer; "When you hear his sermons, you will be able to believe, too")
5. (2) believe -- (credit with veracity; "You cannot believe this man"; "Should we believe a publication like the National Enquirer?")
